result.execSummary:
The defendant Rogelio Guarnero was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing proceeds.   Statements by counsel, Naomi C. and defendant.  

Count 1:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 24 months with 25 days credit; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 18 months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 6 months - consecutive to 13cf5302.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of  3 years - concurrent.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  1) no violations of the criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) do not use or possess any illegally controlled substances; 3) random screening; 4) AODA, treatment or programs; 5) pay costs, assessments and surcharges or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) AODA, treatment or programs as recommended; 3) do not use or possess illegally controlled substances; 4) random screening; 5) do not associate with known gang members.

Defendant waives constitutional rights, enters a plea of GUILTY to Count 1 and is examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum  received and filed. On motion of the State, Court orders Count 2 DISMISSED and read-in for sentencing purposes.
